The article discusses the historic voyage of Leif Erikson and his crew, who are believed to be the first Europeans to reach North America. It highlights the ongoing contributions of Nordic Americans to the diversity and culture of the United States. The article mentions the arrival of Norwegian immigrants in 1825 and the subsequent establishment of Nordic communities across the country. It acknowledges the significant role played by Nordic Americans in various fields such as public service, law enforcement, healthcare, education, and entrepreneurship. The article emphasizes the enduring legacy of Nordic immigrants and the shared values between the United States and Nordic countries. It mentions the annual celebration of Leif Erikson Day on October 9th to honor Nordic-American heritage and calls upon Americans to recognize and celebrate the contributions of Nordic Americans. The article concludes with a proclamation by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. officially designating October 9, 2021, as Leif Erikson Day.